===Etymology 1===
{{root|en|ine-pro|*ǵʰer-|id=yearn}}
From {{inh|en|enm|yerning}}, from {{inh|en|ang|ġierning}}, {{m|ang|ġierninge}}. Equivalent to the [[Appendix:Glossary#gerund|gerund]] ({{m|en|yearn}} + {{m|en|-ing}}). {{m|en|yearn}} comes from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*girnijan}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*girnijaną}}, from {{m|gem-pro|*gernaz||eager, willing}} + {{m|gem-pro|*-janą}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ǵʰer-||to yearn for}}.
====Noun====
{{en-noun}}
# A [[wistful]] or [[melancholy]] [[longing]].
#: ''She had a '''yearning''' to see her long-lost sister again.''
