===Etymology 2===
{{PIE word|en|ḱóm}}
{{root|en|ine-pro|*h₃er-}}
From earlier {{m|en|yerning}}, from {{inh|en|enm|yernyng}}, {{m|enm|erning}}, {{m|enm|renning}}. From {{inh|en|ang|rynning}} and {{m|ang|gerunnen}}, {{m|ang|geurnen||run together, coagulated, curdled}}, past participles of {{m|ang|gerinnan}}, {{m|ang|geirnan}}, respectively. Influenced by {{m+|enm|yern||to (cause to) coagulate or curdle|w=1}}, {{m+|ang|iernan||to run, flow|w=1}}, [[Appendix:Glossary#metathesis|metathesized]] forms derived from the same origin. From verbal prefix {{m|ang|ge-}} + {{m|ang|rinnan||to run}}. First element is from {{der|en|gmw-pro|*ga-}}, from {{der|en|gem-pro|*ga-}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*ḱóm||with, by}}; second element is from {{der|en|gem-pro|*rinnaną}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*h₃r̥-néw-ti}}, from {{m|ine-pro|*h₃er-||to move}}. {{doublet|en|rennet}}, {{doublet|en|run|notext=1}}.
====Noun====
{{en-noun|~}}
# {{lb|en|Scottish|archaic}} [[rennet]] (an enzyme to curdle milk in order to make cheese).
